main event: A witness reported observing an unidentified bright light that was too high and slow to be an airplane, moving in a NE-SW direction in Wakoyni on 7-5-57 at 20:00.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 3 minutes with a single object reported.
The witness described the object as too high and slow to be an airplane, indicating unusual characteristics.
Covington was mentioned as the location where a flashing light was also observed, suggesting potential multiple witnesses or sightings.
The report mentions a possible R/C waterburner, but the data was considered insufficient for evaluation.
The report does not include any photographs of the observed object.
